## Framework 2 — SOC 2

### CC6 — Logical and Physical Access Controls
**CC6.1 — Access Management**
- Missing MFA enforcement for privileged user accounts
- Shared credentials or generic service accounts used across multiple services
- Sensitive data (PII, credentials, keys) not encrypted at rest
- Role-based access control not implemented; all users have equal permissions

**CC6.2 — Authentication and Transmission Security**
- TLS not enforced for all data in transit
- Deprecated TLS versions (1.0, 1.1) or cipher suites (RC4, DES, 3DES) still accepted
- Certificate pinning absent on mobile/client applications handling sensitive data

### CC7 — System Operations
**CC7.1 — Monitoring and Detection**
- No health check endpoints defined
- No alerting configured for abnormal authentication events or error rate spikes
- Application metrics not exposed (no `/metrics`, no Prometheus annotations)

**CC7.2 — Incident Response**
- Centralized logging not implemented; logs scattered across services
- No correlation ID in log entries to trace requests across services
- No runbook or incident response procedure referenced in code/docs

### CC8 — Change Management
**CC8.1 — Change Control**
- No CI/CD pipeline enforcing tests before merge
- Branch protection rules not evident from pipeline config
- No code review requirement visible from CODEOWNERS or branch rules

### A1 — Availability
- No backup mechanism visible for persistent data stores
- No health check or readiness probe defined in Kubernetes/Docker configuration
- No graceful shutdown handler in application code
- Single point of failure: no redundancy or fallback configured

