## Framework 3 — GDPR

### Data Protection Checks
- Personal data in logs: email addresses, IP addresses, full names, phone numbers, national IDs
  Pattern: `logger.*(email|ip|address|phone|ssn|passport)` in log statements
- Analytics loaded without consent gate: Google Analytics, Mixpanel, Segment, Hotjar, Facebook Pixel
  loaded unconditionally at page load without checking consent cookie/flag
- No privacy policy link in frontend application (check `<footer>`, `<nav>`, registration forms)
- User data transmitted to third-party APIs without explicit disclosure in privacy policy
- No data deletion mechanism: no endpoint or admin function to purge user data on request
- No data export mechanism: no DSAR (Data Subject Access Request) handler
- Cookies set without `SameSite`, `Secure`, or `HttpOnly` attributes
- Retention policy not implemented: data accumulated without expiry or archival logic
- PII stored in URL query parameters: `/search?email=user@example.com` (logged by servers/proxies)
- Consent not re-requested when purpose changes; initial consent stored without version/timestamp

