## Framework 5 — PCI-DSS

Apply these checks when code handles payment data, references card processing, or integrates with payment APIs.

### Cardholder Data Environment (CDE) Checks
- PAN (Primary Account Number) patterns in source code, logs, or comments:
  Pattern: `\b(?:4[0-9]{12}(?:[0-9]{3})?|5[1-5][0-9]{14}|3[47][0-9]{13}|6(?:011|5[0-9]{2})[0-9]{12})\b`
- CVV/CVC/CVV2 stored anywhere (Requirement 3.2.1 — strictly prohibited post-authorization)
  Pattern: `cvv`, `cvc`, `security_code` persisted to database or file
- Payment card data transmitted without TLS encryption
- Full PAN logged (even partially masked logging must be reviewed)
- Direct card processing without using an approved payment gateway or tokenization

### Requirement 6 — Secure Systems
- No web application firewall (WAF) referenced in infrastructure config
- Direct internet access to payment-processing servers (missing DMZ/segmentation)
- Patch management not automated for systems in CDE

### Requirement 7/8 — Access Control
- No role-based access to cardholder data; all application roles can read payment tables
- Generic shared accounts used for accessing payment systems
- No MFA on all non-console administrative access to CDE

### Requirement 10 — Audit Logging
- Access to cardholder data not logged with timestamp, user, and action
- Logs not protected from modification (no WORM storage or log forwarding)

### Requirement 11 — Security Testing
- No penetration testing or vulnerability scanning evidence in pipeline
- No file integrity monitoring on critical system files

