## Framework 6 — NIST SP 800-53

### IA-5 — Authenticator Management
- Passwords stored without strong hashing (bcrypt, argon2, scrypt)
- Default credentials not changed in application or infrastructure configuration
- API keys without rotation mechanism or expiry

### AU-2 / AU-12 — Audit Events / Audit Record Generation
- Authentication events (success and failure) not logged
- Privileged actions not logged (admin operations, configuration changes)
- Log entries missing required fields: timestamp, user identity, event type, outcome

### SC-8 — Transmission Confidentiality and Integrity
- Data transmitted over unencrypted channels
- TLS certificate validation disabled: `verify=False`, `rejectUnauthorized: false`, `InsecureSkipVerify: true`
- Sensitive data in GET request URL parameters (logged by intermediaries)

### SC-28 — Protection of Information at Rest
- Database fields containing PII or secrets not encrypted
- Encryption at rest not enabled on storage volumes or database instances (check Terraform)
- Encryption keys stored alongside the data they protect

### SA-11 — Developer Security Testing
- No SAST tool configured in development pipeline
- No DAST tool referenced for pre-production security testing
- Security findings not tracked in issue tracker or project management tool

### CM-6 — Configuration Settings
- Insecure default configuration not hardened before deployment
- Configuration drift not detected (no baseline comparison in pipeline)
- Infrastructure configuration not reviewed for CIS Benchmark alignment

### SI-10 — Information Input Validation
- User inputs accepted without type, length, format, or range validation
- File upload endpoints without MIME type validation and size limits
- GraphQL queries without depth limiting or complexity analysis

---

## Framework 7 — NIST SSDF (SP 800-218)

### PO.1 — Security Requirements
- No SECURITY.md in repository root
- No threat model document referenced in project documentation
- Security requirements absent from feature ticket templates or ADRs

### PS.3 — Protect Software
- Container images not scanned for CVEs before push (Trivy, Grype, Snyk Container)
- No SBOM (Software Bill of Materials) generated in CI/CD pipeline
- Build artifacts not signed or attested (Sigstore/Cosign, SLSA provenance)
- Base image digest not pinned in Dockerfile (use `FROM node:20-alpine@sha256:...`)

### PW.4 — Review the Code
- No SAST tool configured: CodeQL, Semgrep, Bandit (Python), Gosec (Go), SpotBugs (Java)
- SAST not blocking merges on HIGH/CRITICAL findings
- No manual security code review requirement for sensitive changes (auth, crypto, payment)

### PW.5 — Test Executable Code
- No SCA (Software Composition Analysis) in pipeline: Dependabot, Snyk, OWASP Dependency-Check
- Dependency vulnerabilities not blocking merges
- No license compliance check on third-party dependencies

### PW.7 — Remediate Vulnerabilities
- Security findings older than SLA thresholds still open with no mitigation plan
- No CVE triage process visible (no security label in issue tracker)

### RV.1 — Identify and Confirm Vulnerabilities
- No vulnerability disclosure policy (SECURITY.md missing)
- No bug bounty program or responsible disclosure contact
- CVEs in dependencies not tracked after initial scan

