## Audit Command Behavior

When the user types `/security-audit` or "audit this file/project" or "find security issues":

1. **Scan phase**: Check all workspace files matching the configured globs against all framework controls above
2. **Triage phase**: Deduplicate and assign severity per finding
3. **Report structure**:
   - Executive summary (total findings by severity)
   - Findings grouped by severity (CRITICAL first), then by framework
   - Each finding in the standard format above
4. **Compliance dashboard** (score /10 per framework based on controls passing):
   ```
   Framework       Score    Status
   OWASP Top 10    X/10     [PASS/REVIEW/FAIL]
   SOC 2           X/10     [PASS/REVIEW/FAIL]
   GDPR            X/10     [PASS/REVIEW/FAIL]
   ISO 27001       X/10     [PASS/REVIEW/FAIL]
   PCI-DSS         X/10     [N/A if no payment data]
   NIST 800-53     X/10     [PASS/REVIEW/FAIL]
   NIST SSDF       X/10     [PASS/REVIEW/FAIL]
   CIS Benchmarks  X/10     [PASS/REVIEW/FAIL]
   HIPAA           X/10     [N/A if no health data]
   ```
5. **Quick wins**: List all CRITICAL and HIGH findings with estimated fix time under 30 minutes
6. **Remediation roadmap**: Group remaining findings by sprint effort (1 day / 1 week / 1 sprint)

